# RunAnywhere Commons - Exported Symbols
#
# Curated Apple `-exported_symbols_list` for `librac_commons.{a,dylib}`.
# Consumed by `sdk/runanywhere-commons/CMakeLists.txt` and applied at link time
# when commons is built as a shared library (static archives ignore the option).
# Each entry must include the leading underscore (Apple linker convention).
#
# To audit drift vs. RAC_API-decorated declarations in the commons headers:
#   scripts/validation/commons/check_rac_api_exports.sh            # advisory report
#   scripts/validation/commons/check_rac_api_exports.sh --strict   # CI gate (exit 1)
#
# TODO(v0.21): As of 2026-05-05 the include tree exposes 955 RAC_API-decorated
# decls total; 465 are shipped via this exports list, and 490 remain as
# internalization candidates not called by any SDK today. Those should either
# have RAC_API stripped from the header or be relocated to `src/.../internal.h`.
# Once that cleanup lands, wire `check_rac_api_exports.sh --strict` into
# `scripts/validation/commons/run_commons_proto_checks.sh` as a CI gate.
#
# Backend-conditional symbols are split into
# sibling exports files and appended to this list by CMake when the matching
# RAC_BACKEND_* flag is ON:
#   - RACommons.rag.exports               (RAC_BACKEND_RAG)
# When commons is built as a dynamic lib, the appended list keeps every
# RAG symbol resolvable to its backend implementation. When the flag is
# OFF, the symbol does not exist in librac_commons and the Apple
# `-exported_symbols_list` linker would reject an entry naming it —
# hence the split.
#
# The previous onnx_embeddings sibling exports were dropped because those
# `_rac_backend_*_register` symbols live in the engine targets
# (engines/onnx), not in librac_commons.
# Each engine target publishes its own exports list.
#
# The previously-stale rac_vad_{start,stop,reset} RAC_API
# decls have been deleted from include/rac/features/vad/rac_vad_service.h.
# Callers use rac_vad_component_{start,stop,reset} (struct API) or
# rac_vad_{start,stop,reset}_lifecycle_proto (proto ABI) instead.

# Audio Utilities — internal helpers (PCM/WAV plumbing for backends and
# tests). Audio bytes leaving the SDK travel inside generated proto results.

