_rac_http_download_cancel

# Events — internal lower-level publisher used by lifecycle manager,
# storage analyzer, device manager, and engine plugins for telemetry
# breadcrumbs. Public SDK event stream is rac_sdk_event_* below.

# Lifecycle / Model Management / Model Paths / Model Registry / Model
# Assignment / Framework Utilities / Module Registry — non-proto
# struct-based APIs are internal commons helpers (still used by JNI
# during migration). SDK-facing surfaces use the proto-byte ABIs:
# rac_model_lifecycle_*_proto, rac_model_registry_*_proto,
# rac_component_lifecycle_snapshot_proto. Plugin selection is on
# rac_plugin_* (rac_plugin_find / rac_plugin_find_for_engine) in rac/plugin/.

# LLM Component — non-proto component create/load/generate/etc. APIs are
# now internal (used by JNI bridge during migration). SDK-facing surface is
# the proto-byte ABI (rac_llm_*_proto / rac_llm_set_stream_proto_callback)
# below. Thinking helpers (rac_llm_extract_thinking et al.) moved to
# internal — SDKs read thinking splits from LLMGenerationResult bytes.
# (See docs/CPP_PROTO_OWNERSHIP.md.)

# LoRA Registry — non-proto APIs are internal helpers. SDK-facing LoRA
# surface is the rac_lora_*_proto family below.

